    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-08-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-08-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="557" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d557">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-08-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 26, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.
                                (Received, Sept. 7.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 603.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that the
                            murderer of Mr. Stupe, of whose first trial you were informed in my No.
                            537, of May 5, 1895, has been sentenced on retrial to fifteen years’
                            imprisonment.</p>
                <p>The reversal of the first judgment by the court of cassation without the
                            presence of the consular dragoman caused my protest to the Porte, copy
                            of which was sent you in my dispatch No. 529, of May 3, 1895. The result
                            of retrial was as gratifying as it was unexpected.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
